Four men were arrested for armed robbery in Umzimkhulu, KwaZulu-Natal, on Thursday morning. A police source said the four men allegedly robbed a shop of 163 cellphones and about R60 000 cash Three firearms were also recovered during the arrest. Members of the Pietermaritzburg highway patrol, the Hawks, Magma Security and SSS Security received information about the incident and intercepted the car on Umlaas Road, outside Pietermaritzburg, shortly after the alleged robber. Police were yet to comment on the matter. *This is a developing story.